modules.description: Performs cryptographic transformations on 64-byte strings using optimized C-implemented Salsa20 core algorithms, including 20, 8, and 12 rounds. Processes input keys, nonces, and counters to generate pseudorandom byte sequences. Used in stream cipher implementations for secure data encryption and decryption.

Processes 16 32-bit blocks through Salsa20/8, Salsa20/12, and Salsa20/20 core transformations, producing encrypted output blocks. Accepts and returns strings representing fixed-size binary data. Used in cryptographic implementations requiring reduced-round Salsa20 variants for performance or security analysis.
